"--smush-placeholder-width: 53px; --smush-placeholder-aspect-ratio: 53/53;"=
><h3 id=3D"headline-1133-4013" class=3D"ct-headline">Lognormal</h3><div id=
=3D"text_block-1193-4013" class=3D"ct-text-block"><div style=3D"text-align:=
 center;">Values are positively skewed, not symmetric like a normal distrib=
ution. It is used to represent values that don=E2=80=99t go below zero but =
have unlimited positive potential. Examples of variables described by logno=
rmal distributions include real estate property values, stock prices, and o=
il reserves. <br></div></div></div><div id=3D"div_block-1214-4013" class=3D=
"ct-div-block box-link white-background"><img id=3D"image-1135-4013" alt=3D=
