ss=3D"ct-text-block"><div style=3D"text-align: center;">The user defines th=
e minimum, most likely, and maximum values, just like the triangular distri=
bution. Values around the most likely value have a higher chance of occurri=
ng. However, values between the most likely and extremes are more likely to=
 occur than the triangular; that is, the extremes are not as emphasized. An=
 example of the use of a PERT distribution is to describe the duration of a=
 task in a project management model. <br></div></div></div><div id=3D"div_b=
lock-1237-4013" class=3D"ct-div-block box-link white-background"><img id=3D=
